Wash and dry all produce. Peel and halve @carrots{1}(peeled and halved lengthwise) into half-moons. Halve, peel, and thinly slice @red onion{1}(peeled and thinly sliced); mince a few slices until you have 3 TBSP. Core, deseed, and thinly slice @green bell pepper{1}(cored and thinly sliced). Zest @lime{1} until you have 1 tsp; quarter lime. Finely chop @cilantro{1/4%ounce}(finely chopped).

Melt 1 TBSP @butter{2%tablespoon} in a #medium pot{} over medium-high heat. Add carrot, minced onion, and ½ tsp @turmeric{1%tsp}(we sent more). Cook until fragrant, ~{1-2%minutes}. Add 1¼ cups water, 1 @chicken stock concentrate{2} and a large pinch of @salt{pinch}. Bring to a boil, then stir in @jasmine rice{3/4%cup}. Cover, reduce heat to low, and cook until tender, about ~{15%minutes}. Turn off heat. Stir in @peas{4%ounce} and half the cilantro. Season with salt and @pepper{}. Keep covered until ready to serve.

Add @black beans{13.4%ounce}(undrained) to a #small pot{}. Bring to a boil, then reduce heat to low and stir in 1 TBSP butter, 2 tsp @blackening spice{2%tablespoon}, and a pinch of salt and pepper. Using a #potato masher{} or #fork{}, mash about half the beans. Keep covered until ready to serve. In a #small bowl{}, combine @sour cream{6%tablespoon}, lime zest, and juice from 2 lime wedges. Season with salt and pepper.

Heat a large drizzle of @vegetable oil{4%teaspoon} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add sliced onion, bell pepper, and a pinch of salt and pepper. Cook, stirring, until softened and slightly charred, ~{6-8%minutes}. Transfer to a #large bowl{}. Heat another large drizzle of oil in same pan over medium-high heat. Add @Italian chicken sausage{18%ounce}(casings removed) and remaining Blackening Spice. Cook, breaking up meat with a #spoon{}, until cooked through, ~{5-7%minutes}.

Add veggies, remaining stock concentrate, and 1/2 cup water to pan with sausage. Simmer until slightly reduced, ~{1-2%minutes}. Fluff rice with a fork. Set aside a third of the rice, a third of the beans, and half the sausage mixture for lunch. Divide remaining rice, beans, and sausage mixture between plates. Top with lime crema, remaining cilantro, and, if desired, 1 tsp @hot sauce{3%teaspoon}. Serve remaining lime wedges on the side for squeezing over.

> The Southwest Roll-Up Lunch nutrition information is as follows: Calories: 760, Fat: 30 g, Saturated Fat: 12 g, Carbohydrate: 78 g, Sugar: 10 g, Fiber: 8 g, Protein: 43 g, Cholesterol: 120 mg, Sodium: 1870 mg. The nutrition facts panel below represents the nutrient values for the Chicken Sausage and Peppers Bowl Dinner.

Divide reserved rice, beans and sausage mixture between #reusable containers{}. Pack @flour tortilla{2}, remaining sour cream, and remaining hot sauce on the side. When ready to eat, microwave rice, beans, and sausage mixture on high until warm. Wrap in tortillas and serve with sour cream and hot sauce on the side.